<l>urupiya ṉilaiyu moḻiyumā ruḷavē</l>
<l>yāvayiṉ valleḻut tiyaṟkai yākum</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>There are words [ending in <foreign xml:lang="ta">ō</foreign>] which behave [in the same ways</l>
<l>as when they are followed by] case-suffixes. In such cases,</l>
<l>the plosive becomes unchanged.<note
              place="foot">This again refers to <foreign xml:lang="ta">kō</foreign> which may have the empty-morph <foreign xml:lang="ta">-oṉ : kō + kai &gt; kōoṉkai.</foreign></note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
